03/09/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- European Commission Ambassador Lutz Saltzman and Albanian Integration Minister Ermelinda Meksi signed an agreement Thursday (2 September) on the implementation of community projects in the Western Balkans. 
Saltzman said the projects would be funded under the CARDS programme, with financing provided as of next year. 
He added that Albania and other countries in the region would be eligible for the structural funds if they submit clear and concrete projects aimed at attracting investments. 
Funds to be allocated under the programme total 4.6m euros. 
(ATA - 02/09/04)
